                        <head>154. Summary of Conclusions of a Meeting of the Washington Special
                            Actions Group<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d154fn1">Source: National
                                Archives, <persName corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName> Presidential
                                Materials, <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files, <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Institutional Files (H-Files), Box
                                H–115, <gloss target="#t_WSAG1">WSAG</gloss> Meetings Minutes,
                                Originals, 1971. Top Secret; <gloss target="#t_Nodis1">Nodis</gloss>; <gloss target="#t_COMINT1">COMINT</gloss>. The
                                meeting took place in the Situation Room of the White House.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" from="1971-03-16T17:10:00-05:00" to="1971-03-16T18:40:00-05:00">March 16, 1971, 5:10–6:40 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline></opener>
                        <list type="subject">
                            <head>SUBJECT</head>
                            <item>Intelligence on North Vietnamese Supply Movements</item>
                        </list>
