                        <p rend="center">SUMMARY</p>
                        <p>The <gloss target="#t_WSAG1">WSAG</gloss> received a briefing on the
                            methodology employed in preparing intelligence estimates of supply
                            movements along the <persName corresp="#p_HCM1">Ho Chi Minh</persName>
                            <pb facs="0504" n="465" xml:id="pg_465"/> Trail. In the accompanying
                            discussion, the <gloss target="#t_WSAG1">WSAG</gloss> considered the
                            discrepancies between <gloss target="#t_CIA1">CIA</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_DIA1">DIA</gloss> estimates and the problems involved in
                            comparing data from different years and in assessing the impact of the
                                <gloss target="#t_LAMSON7191">Lam Son</gloss> operation on enemy
                            supply throughput. It was agreed to hold a second <gloss target="#t_WSAG1">WSAG</gloss> meeting to discuss these topics
                            further.</p>
                        <p>[Omitted here are the minutes of the meeting.]</p>
